Atlas Arteria (ALX.AX) Price Target Bull Case Base Case Bear Case Updated Components EPS Investment Thesis Bull Base Bear Scenarios Risks to Price Target / Rating
We tweak our ALX price target to A\\$5.11/share (- 3cps) after incorporating:
- ALX's 1H25 results and 3Q25 traffic commentary; and- A regular mark-to-market for bond yields and exchange rates, and rolling forward our running NPV from 30 July 2025 to 28 August 2025.

EPS is not a meaningful measure for ALX, owing to the mix of consolidated and equity accounting, and other investment structures. Having said that, we lift our EPS estimates over FY25- 27e by \(+3\%\) on traffic assumptions and other minor tweaks.
We keep our bull case value unchanged, but lower our bear case value by \(1\%\) reflecting leverage.

ALX targets future distributions of at least 40cps, based on a 90- 110% payout of FCF (with capital releases used to offset debt amortisation impacting on distributions, and any further capital releases to be used for special distributions or buybacks).
We forecast steady FCF growth from the APRR, Skyway, and Warnow Tunnel, and no distributions from the Dulles Greenway (in debt lockup until at least 2030 absent a restructuring).

ALX has FCF flexibility via Skyway capital releases, and corporate cash. Risk- adjusted returns for ALX are median for our stock coverage on a 12- month view, including some prospect for corporate activity, but with near- term French policy uncertainty.
Source: Refinitiv, Morgan Stanley Research
